      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QOI (hemolysis index) must be identical to the clinical decision QOI, with no surrogate or proxy metrics accepted at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) as proxy; the clinical decision QOI is plasma free haemoglobin (pfHb) concentration. The mapping between NIH and pfHb introduces unquantified uncertainty. Achieved level 3 does not satisfy required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
